1
00:00:36,267 --> 00:00:39,333
<i>I'll give a 100,000 pesos
as reward.</i>

2
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:42,767
<i>As long as someone can tell me
where my kids' dad is.</i>

3
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,367
<i>Are you sure you know
where my dad is?</i>

4
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,433
<i>Yes, I went with them
to deliver it to her.</i>

5
00:00:46,567 --> 00:00:48,000
<i>How can we be sure
you're not a scammer?</i>

6
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:49,133
<i>You're not fooling us, are you?</i>

7
00:00:49,267 --> 00:00:51,800
<i>Manuel Cruz is paraplegic, okay?</i>

8
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:53,267
<i> I'll match their reward.</i>

9
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,333
<i> I'm planning to charge</i>

10
00:00:54,467 --> 00:00:56,267
<i> them of 200,000 pesos.</i>

11
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:57,333
<i> I dare you.</i>

12
00:00:57,467 --> 00:01:00,133
<i>By tomorrow,
everyone on social media</i>

13
00:01:00,267 --> 00:01:01,900
<i>will be aware of your plate
cloning business.</i>

14
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:03,933
<i>Just send the 100,000 pesos
to my account.</i>

15
00:01:04,967 --> 00:01:06,133
<i>It looks like
he's messing with us.</i>

16
00:01:06,267 --> 00:01:07,167
<i> I can't reach him, either.</i>

17
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:08,267
<i> So annoying!</i>

18
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:10,667
<i>When are Felma
and the kids coming?</i>

19
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,700
<i> Can't it just be us for now?</i>

20
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:13,967
<i> We're done.</i>

21
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:15,133
<i> Manuel, not yet.</i>

22
00:01:15,267 --> 00:01:17,033
<i>Not for you,
but fo me, it's yes.</i>

23
00:01:17,167 --> 00:01:18,667
<i> What do I need to do?</i>

24
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,367
<i> I won't change my mind.</i>

25
00:01:22,067 --> 00:01:23,567
<i>I'll go through with
the annulment.</i>

26
00:01:30,133 --> 00:01:31,600
That can't be, Manuel.

27
00:01:32,633 --> 00:01:34,300
You can't leave me.

28
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:38,267
You can't leave me
for that mistress!

29
00:01:41,667 --> 00:01:43,333
That can't be!

30
00:01:43,467 --> 00:01:45,000
No!

31
00:01:47,367 --> 00:01:48,633
I'm your wife.

32
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:49,933
I'm your wife.

33
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:52,167
I'm the only Mrs. Cruz.

34
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:55,333
I'm the one and only
Mrs. Hazel Capistrano-Cruz.

35
00:01:55,467 --> 00:01:57,467
Only me! No one else!
It should only be me.

36
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,467
Only me!

37
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,767
What were you talking about?

38
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:02,067
Annulment?

39
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,567
Annulment? No!

40
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:05,467
Annulment.

41
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,067
We'll have to kill
each other first

42
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,500
before those papers
reach the court.

43
00:02:10,533 --> 00:02:11,767
And that Felma!

44
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:13,667
Felma! That Felma... again!

45
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,900
Felma, huh!

46
00:02:15,067 --> 00:02:16,233
You're a mistress!

47
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:17,333
You're no match!

48
00:02:17,467 --> 00:02:19,433
You're no match for me!

49
00:02:19,567 --> 00:02:20,633
You're just a mistress!

50
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:23,333
If necessary...

51
00:02:23,467 --> 00:02:26,000
one of you has to disappear

52
00:02:26,133 --> 00:02:27,633
so that you can't
get back together.

53
00:02:27,767 --> 00:02:28,733
So you can't end up together.

54
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,267
Fine...

55
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,500
fine, you choose.

56
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:35,667
Choose which one of you
I'll throw into hell.

57
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,733
<i> I have something to confess.</i>

58
00:02:39,867 --> 00:02:42,100
<i> Your mom is my best friend,</i>

59
00:02:42,233 --> 00:02:45,467
<i> but... I'm scared of her.</i>

60
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:46,500
<i> Why?</i>

61
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:48,933
<i>She's capable of doing
things that...</i>

62
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:51,367
<i> you'd never imagine.</i>

63
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,067
<i> So just follow her.</i>

64
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,333
<i> Trust me.</i>

65
00:02:54,467 --> 00:02:56,633
<i> She's a terrifying enemy.</i>

66
00:03:22,367 --> 00:03:23,567
Jessica.

67
00:03:24,867 --> 00:03:26,867
Dear, what did your mom
do to you?

68
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:29,267
No, Dad.

69
00:03:30,333 --> 00:03:31,667
Mom has changed.

70
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,900
I think you've noticed it, too.

71
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,567
Yes, Dear.

72
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,533
I definitely notice.

73
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,167
You can say...

74
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:46,000
I'm a bad person.

75
00:03:46,667 --> 00:03:48,433
but I think...

76
00:03:48,567 --> 00:03:50,200
everything she does...

77
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:54,100
and says isn't real.

78
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:57,200
It's all fake,
I can see through her.

79
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,667
Dad, no.

80
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,933
Dad, no.

81
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:04,333
Dear...

82
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:06,267
You too, do you really think so?

83
00:04:09,133 --> 00:04:10,433
Dear...

84
00:04:10,567 --> 00:04:11,567
You're so obvious,

85
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:14,100
You keep praising her.

86
00:04:14,233 --> 00:04:15,800
Jessica, tell me the truth.

87
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:19,033
Huh?

88
00:04:19,167 --> 00:04:20,967
Huh, Dear?

89
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:24,100
Is everything your mom does
genuine or not?

90
00:04:26,067 --> 00:04:28,133
Because I feel...

91
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:30,267
that she's just fooling me.

92
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:34,033
And you.

93
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:36,067
You? Are you in cahoots
with her?

94
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,533
Jessica, tell me the truth.

95
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:45,033
<i>- Mom, Mom!
- Who are you calling, huh?</i>

96
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:47,333
<i>- Who are you calling... Felma?
- Mom!</i>

97
00:04:47,467 --> 00:04:48,867
<i>- Who?
- Mom!</i>

98
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,700
<i>They won't stop looking for Dad.</i>

99
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:54,100
<i>Once they find out where we are,</i>

100
00:04:54,233 --> 00:04:55,600
<i> that can only mean one thing.</i>

101
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:57,167
<i> Someone betrayed me.</i>

102
00:04:58,333 --> 00:05:00,633
<i> And it's you.</i>

103
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,400
Dad, Dad, I'm sorry.

104
00:05:03,533 --> 00:05:05,933
Dad, I'm scared of Mom.

105
00:05:06,067 --> 00:05:07,933
I can't defy her.

106
00:05:09,733 --> 00:05:11,467
Dad, I'm sorry.

107
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:14,800
I'm scared of Mom.

108
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:16,667
Dad, I'm sorry.

109
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:21,033
I knew it.

110
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:24,633
I know you so well, Dear.

111
00:05:24,767 --> 00:05:27,267
I know when you're lying.

112
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,700
Dear...

113
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:30,400
Did she hurt you?

114
00:05:30,533 --> 00:05:31,633
Huh?

115
00:05:32,633 --> 00:05:33,733
Tell me.

116
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:36,500
Did she hurt you?

117
00:05:41,733 --> 00:05:43,300
You're a monster, Hazel!

118
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,767
- Ouch.
- Dad.

119
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:50,667
- Dad, Dad.
- Oh, oh, oh.

120
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:54,800
- Dad, you're still weak.
- Where is she?

121
00:05:54,933 --> 00:05:56,000
Where's your mom?

122
00:05:56,133 --> 00:05:57,733
Dad, don't force it.

123
00:05:57,867 --> 00:05:59,500
Jessica.

124
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:00,933
Dad, be careful.

125
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,267
Dear, I'm sorry.

126
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:07,367
Sorry.

127
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,567
I'm sorry, Dear,
I can't protect you.

128
00:06:10,733 --> 00:06:13,133
It's always my fault

129
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:15,467
that your mom hurts you.

130
00:06:16,933 --> 00:06:19,300
And I'm always left powerless.

131
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:21,667
<i> Dad feels sad, Mom.</i>

132
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,633
<i>He just wants to feel
like someone still loves</i>

133
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:25,600
<i>and cares for him
apart from me.</i>

134
00:06:25,733 --> 00:06:28,200
<i>Maybe he can find that
in my half-sister as well,</i>

135
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:30,400
<i>because he clearly
isn't getting it from you.</i>

136
00:06:30,533 --> 00:06:31,567
<i> How dare you?</i>

137
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:34,067
<i>- How dare you? Huh? Huh?
- Hazel! Hazel, stop!</i>

138
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,600
<i> Don't hurt Jessica!</i>

139
00:06:35,733 --> 00:06:39,133
I can't defend you
all the time, Dear.

140
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:40,600
Jessica...

141
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:45,533
Jessica, I'm sorry.

142
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:50,033
Dear, I'm sorry for not being
able to defend you.

143
00:06:50,667 --> 00:06:52,300
Dad.

144
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,367
Sorry, Dear.

145
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:56,900
Dad.

146
00:06:57,033 --> 00:06:59,733
Dad, you didn't do
anything wrong.

147
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:02,200
It's Mommy, Dad.

148
00:07:02,333 --> 00:07:06,067
Dad, I'll find a way
to escape Mom.

149
00:07:07,633 --> 00:07:09,133
We've done it before.

150
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:11,400
We can do it again, Dad.

151
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:15,933
Dad, regain your strength, okay?

152
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,033
Dad.

153
00:07:25,267 --> 00:07:26,400
Big Sister.

154
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:28,233
I'm going to sleep here
tonight, okay?

155
00:07:29,567 --> 00:07:31,000
Huh?

156
00:07:31,133 --> 00:07:32,200
I don't want to.

157
00:07:32,333 --> 00:07:34,400
You're just going to pester me,
you never stop talking.

158
00:07:34,533 --> 00:07:36,500
I won't be able to sleep
because of you.

159
00:07:36,633 --> 00:07:37,667
Of course, Big Sister.

160
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:40,433
You missed a lot of moments.

161
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:42,367
So I will tell you everything.

162
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:45,700
And you know what, Big Sister?

163
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:48,500
We're almost complete...

164
00:07:50,167 --> 00:07:52,533
only one is missing.

165
00:07:52,667 --> 00:07:55,467
Coleen, don't worry.

166
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:58,567
Just a little more time,
and Dad will be with us.

167
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:02,133
Mom and Jeff don't stop
looking for him.

168
00:08:02,267 --> 00:08:03,433
Just a little more time.

169
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:06,600
It's so frustrating.

170
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:09,533
Oh, why?

171
00:08:09,667 --> 00:08:11,400
The man I talked to seemed
to be messing with us.

172
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:12,567
He didn't show up, Big brother?

173
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:13,767
He didn't.

174
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:16,233
And we couldn't reach him
when we were there.

175
00:08:16,367 --> 00:08:17,433
And he texted just now.

176
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:19,000
He said he couldn't come
because there was an emergency.

177
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:20,767
And he told me to send him
the reward

178
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:22,200
before he tells me where Dad is.

179
00:08:22,367 --> 00:08:23,633
He surely is a scammer.

180
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:29,033
Just like me...

181
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:30,200
Scammer.

182
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:32,033
Andrea, you're not a scammer.

183
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,267
You were also scammed.

184
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:37,967
But my colleagues, my friends,

185
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:40,267
the FMP staff...

186
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:42,533
I scammed them.

187
00:08:42,667 --> 00:08:44,433
I dragged them into it.

188
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:46,267
And then I let Mom handle it.

189
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:51,067
Andrea, forget about it.

190
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,633
She's not asking you
to pay her, right?

191
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:54,767
That's right.

192
00:08:54,933 --> 00:08:57,833
Andeng, we owe Mom a lot, but...

193
00:08:58,567 --> 00:09:00,733
maybe it's enough
that we came back here...

194
00:09:00,867 --> 00:09:02,233
and in FMP.

195
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:05,600
Where's Mom?

196
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:06,867
You were together, right?

197
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,333
She was on the phone earlier.

198
00:09:08,467 --> 00:09:09,467
Yes.

199
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,900
Yes, thank you so much
for your help.

200
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:12,233
I will check it now.

201
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,200
Dear, can I borrow
your laptop, please?

202
00:09:18,567 --> 00:09:21,167
The private investigator
emailed me.

203
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:23,033
Colonel Sarabia's referral.

204
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:25,933
What is it, Mom?
What's going on?

205
00:09:28,967 --> 00:09:31,333
Your dad could be in Bulacan.

206
00:09:31,467 --> 00:09:34,033
But the private investigator
couldn't follow,

207
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:35,667
because the van
was already full.

208
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:36,800
It left right away.

209
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:38,533
There are only two options, Mom.

210
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:42,633
Hazel could've brought him
either to Marilao or Meycauayan.

211
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:45,533
Wait, Son,
we're not sure yet.

212
00:09:45,667 --> 00:09:50,333
Who knows? Maybe it wasn't
Hazel that Alice visited.

213
00:09:50,467 --> 00:09:53,267
But there's a big possibility
that it was her.

214
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,167
Who else?

215
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,200
Yes, Mom.

216
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:57,800
At least, we have a lead.

217
00:09:58,633 --> 00:10:00,033
There's hope.

218
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:01,533
Yes, my dear children.

219
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:03,267
They'll find out if...

220
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:06,167
Hazel has relatives in Bulacan.

221
00:10:11,567 --> 00:10:13,667
I can do this forever, Manuel.

222
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:17,000
I won't get tired
of taking care of you.

223
00:10:20,033 --> 00:10:21,267
By the way,

224
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:23,900
you have a check-up with the
doctor next week.

225
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:26,700
In the hospital?

226
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,600
No.

227
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:32,667
I asked my college friend,
who's a doctor, to come here.

228
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:37,200
By the way, I bought milkfish.

229
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:38,533
How do you want it cooked?

230
00:10:38,667 --> 00:10:41,233
Would you like sinigang?

231
00:10:41,367 --> 00:10:42,700
Or steamed?

232
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:43,967
Anything but fried.

233
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:45,433
It's up to you.

234
00:10:46,733 --> 00:10:49,300
Veggies?

235
00:10:49,433 --> 00:10:50,400
I bought a lot of veggies.

236
00:10:50,533 --> 00:10:52,400
What would you like to have?
Mixed veggies?

237
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:54,167
Chopsuey? Pinakbet?

238
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:56,100
No, whatever you like to cook.

239
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:01,000
Manuel, is there a problem?

240
00:11:02,267 --> 00:11:03,567
It seems like...

241
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:04,967
you're not in the mood.

242
00:11:06,367 --> 00:11:07,467
Nothing.

243
00:11:24,133 --> 00:11:26,300
How can Dad and I escape?

244
00:11:29,967 --> 00:11:32,700
<i> Ma'am, where am I?</i>

245
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:34,267
This is Camalig, Dear.

246
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,600
<i> here is, Meycauayan.</i>

247
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:37,967
Jessica.

248
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:45,067
What's your Dad's problem?

249
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,500
I don't know, Mommy.

250
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:48,967
What did you tell him?

251
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,300
Nothing.

252
00:11:51,433 --> 00:11:54,200
I just told him the things
you wanted me to say.

253
00:11:59,433 --> 00:12:00,767
Hello, Alice.

254
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:01,800
Oh?

255
00:12:01,933 --> 00:12:03,500
Are you almost here?

256
00:12:03,633 --> 00:12:05,633
<i> I decided not to go, friend.</i>

257
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:08,667
<i>I saw a guy on a motorcycle
outside the condo.</i>

258
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,233
<i>I think I also saw him
at Southcrest.</i>

259
00:12:11,367 --> 00:12:13,433
<i>I feel that someone's
watching me.</i>

260
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:15,967
Is that so?

261
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,400
It could be Jeffrey.

262
00:12:18,533 --> 00:12:20,300
I saw him the other day.

263
00:12:20,433 --> 00:12:22,567
<i>I don't know,
he's wearing a helmet.</i>

264
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,900
<i>I'm also not sure
if he's spying on me,</i>

265
00:12:25,033 --> 00:12:26,600
<i> or if I'm just being paranoid.</i>

266
00:12:26,733 --> 00:12:28,867
<i> It's better to be careful.</i>

267
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:29,933
Never mind, okay.

268
00:12:30,067 --> 00:12:31,500
Don't come here for now.

269
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:34,333
<i>Friend, if someone's
really watching me,</i>

270
00:12:34,467 --> 00:12:36,667
<i>it only means Felma and her
children won't stop.</i>

271
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,733
<i> I'm worried.</i>

272
00:12:37,867 --> 00:12:39,567
<i> How long can you hide Manuel</i>

273
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,567
<i> without being traced by them?</i>

274
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:42,800
Not for long, Alice.

275
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:46,267
Once Manuel's condition
improves...

276
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:48,800
I will bring him back to Canada,
even if against his will.

277
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,933
If I have to sedate him
heavily...

278
00:12:53,067 --> 00:12:54,967
I will.

279
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:17,967
Lord Jesus...

280
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:23,400
this family and I pray...

281
00:13:23,567 --> 00:13:26,067
that wherever Manuel
is right now...

282
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,767
he's safe and in good condition.

283
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:31,133
Protect him, Lord God.

284
00:13:31,267 --> 00:13:33,133
Guide him home safely.

285
00:13:34,167 --> 00:13:35,933
Heal his wound...

286
00:13:36,067 --> 00:13:37,867
and those of this family.

287
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,533
This is our prayer...

288
00:13:40,567 --> 00:13:42,300
- Amen.
- Amen.

289
00:13:42,433 --> 00:13:44,567
In the name of the Father,
the Son, Holy Spirit. Amen.

290
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:48,600
Father, Father Bong,
thank you so much.

291
00:13:48,733 --> 00:13:50,533
You're welcome, Felma.

292
00:13:50,667 --> 00:13:53,767
Just... don't lose hope.

293
00:13:54,567 --> 00:13:56,300
You will find Manuel.

294
00:13:56,433 --> 00:13:58,867
Yes, thank you.

295
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:01,900
Father, would you like to have
some snacks first?

296
00:14:02,033 --> 00:14:02,967
No, thank you.

297
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:04,633
I still have an appointment.

298
00:14:04,767 --> 00:14:07,067
Okay, Didang,
please walk him out.

299
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,567
I'll take you there first.

300
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:09,733
- Please help him.
- Yes, Mom.

301
00:14:09,867 --> 00:14:12,333
Yes, yes, go on.

302
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:13,533
Take care of Father, okay?

303
00:14:13,667 --> 00:14:17,300
- I will.
- Father, thank you.

304
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:19,100
- Dear.
- Mom.

305
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:21,567
Mom, I'm sorry we couldn't make
it on time.

306
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:23,700
It took a long time before
Joel could get checked.

307
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,567
There were so many patients.

308
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:28,267
Ah.

309
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:32,033
Mom, this is Joel.

310
00:14:32,167 --> 00:14:33,133
Good day, Ma'am.

311
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:36,100
We've finally met.

312
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:39,200
Thank you so much for all
the help you gave my daughter.

313
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:40,467
Don't mention it.

314
00:14:42,067 --> 00:14:45,333
Continue your conversation
while we eat.

315
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:47,733
This is my godmother,
Auntie Paz.

316
00:14:47,867 --> 00:14:49,167
- Auntie Paz.
- Hello.

317
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:51,167
My sister, Coleen.

318
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:52,767
And, of course,
you know Jeffrey.

319
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:54,433
And my godfather.

320
00:14:54,567 --> 00:14:55,833
Auntie Paz's husband.

321
00:14:55,967 --> 00:14:56,833
- Come on.
- Okay.

322
00:14:56,967 --> 00:14:58,500
Go on and eat.

323
00:14:58,633 --> 00:15:00,067
- Thank you.
- So we can get to know

324
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:02,567
- Joel better.
- Auntie! Get to know?

325
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:07,133
- Nothing, I said nothing.
- There's no such thing.

326
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:09,300
Hello?

327
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,600
Is this...

328
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:13,800
Didang.

329
00:15:13,933 --> 00:15:15,033
Really?

330
00:15:17,033 --> 00:15:18,000
Oh, thank you.

331
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:22,267
My children,

332
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:23,533
good news.

333
00:15:23,667 --> 00:15:27,100
The private investigator
got some information.

334
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:31,333
Hazel studied elementary and
high school in Bulacan.

335
00:15:32,967 --> 00:15:34,700
- Answered prayer.
- It's just right!

336
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:36,400
Thank You, Lord.

337
00:15:36,533 --> 00:15:38,400
- Thank you!
- Yes, Bulacan.

338
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:42,067
Thank You, Lord, that was fast.

339
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,300
- Oh, right?
- That was fast.

340
00:15:43,433 --> 00:15:45,133
- Really, answered prayer!
- Thank God!

341
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:09,500
Dad! Dad!

342
00:17:09,633 --> 00:17:10,533
Jessica.

343
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:13,967
Dad, dad,
I took Mom's phone.

344
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:15,333
Huh?

345
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:17,400
Your mom might catch you.

346
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,400
No, Dad, Mom's sleeping soundly.

347
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:26,667
Dad, let's call Auntie Felma
for help.

348
00:17:27,567 --> 00:17:29,500
I thought there wasn't any
signal here?

349
00:17:30,467 --> 00:17:31,733
Mommy lied.

350
00:17:33,167 --> 00:17:34,700
There's a signal here, Dad,

351
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,700
but only near the door
and downstairs.

352
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:38,733
Dad, what's Auntie
Felma's number?

353
00:17:38,867 --> 00:17:40,567
I didn't memorize it.

354
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:47,667
- zero, nine, seven, two...
- zero... nine... seven... two.

355
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,000
Oh...

356
00:17:49,167 --> 00:17:51,433
- Nine, two...
- Nine, two...

357
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:54,233
I think six...

358
00:17:55,467 --> 00:17:58,400
Dear, Dear, sorry,

359
00:17:58,533 --> 00:18:01,067
I didn't memorize your Auntie
Felma's number.

360
00:18:01,667 --> 00:18:03,433
- Dad, try to remember.
- six...

361
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:06,400
- six...
- Oh, no.

362
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:17,200
Tomorrow, I'll go to Meycauayan
and Marilao.

363
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:18,533
I'll ask around if there
are Capistranos there.

364
00:18:18,667 --> 00:18:20,100
They might know Hazel.

365
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,200
I'll go with you, Jeff,
I'll help you.

366
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:23,600
Me, too.

367
00:18:24,933 --> 00:18:26,167
Capistrano?

368
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,367
Yes, Joel.

369
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:31,967
Hazel's surname was Capistrano
before she became Cruz.

370
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:34,000
Hazel Capistrano.

371
00:18:34,133 --> 00:18:36,967
I know some Capistranos
in Bulacan.

372
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:39,500
Who knows?
Maybe they know Hazel.

373
00:18:41,467 --> 00:18:42,833
I'll start from there.

374
00:18:42,967 --> 00:18:45,800
Joel, I need the details
of the people you know.

375
00:18:45,933 --> 00:18:46,833
Sure, I'll give it to you.

376
00:18:46,967 --> 00:18:48,133
Okay.

377
00:18:48,267 --> 00:18:51,133
Dad, try to remember, please.

378
00:18:52,467 --> 00:18:54,233
Sorry, Dear.

379
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,800
I really can't remember.

380
00:18:57,267 --> 00:18:58,567
Abel's number.

381
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,567
Yes, I memorized it.

382
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,000
Okay, okay, Dad.

383
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:04,867
Zero... zero, nine, seven, two.

384
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,133
Zero, nine, seven, two.

385
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:10,700
- Five, three, eight...
- Five, three, eight...

386
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:13,667
- Seven, three...
- Seven, three...

387
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,767
- Nine, one.
- Nine, one.

388
00:19:21,167 --> 00:19:22,600
Dad, it's ringing.

389
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:26,700
It's ringing.

390
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:32,967
Hello?

391
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:34,267
Hello, Uncle Abel.

392
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:36,600
<i> This is Jessica.</i>

393
00:19:36,733 --> 00:19:37,700
Jessica?

394
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:40,700
Jessica!

395
00:19:42,467 --> 00:19:43,900
Hello!

396
00:19:44,033 --> 00:19:45,833
Uncle Abel, this is Jessica.

397
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,233
Hello?

398
00:19:48,367 --> 00:19:49,367
Uncle Abel,

399
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:50,933
do you hear me?

400
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:52,400
Your line is choppy, Dear.

401
00:19:52,933 --> 00:19:54,633
Hello? Wait.

402
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:58,133
- Jessica?
<i> - Uncle Abel?</i>

403
00:19:58,267 --> 00:20:00,033
<i> - do you hear me?
</i>- Hello?

404
00:20:00,167 --> 00:20:01,267
It's still choppy.

405
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:03,167
Louder,
I can't hear you.

406
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:04,400
Hello?

407
00:20:05,033 --> 00:20:06,100
Jessica?

408
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:08,733
<i> Jessica, Dear.</i>

409
00:20:08,867 --> 00:20:10,100
Where are you and your dad?

410
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:14,633
Jessica, where are you now?

411
00:20:14,767 --> 00:20:16,300
Uncle, we're in Bulacan.

412
00:20:16,433 --> 00:20:17,933
Bulacan,
they're in Bulacan.

413
00:20:18,067 --> 00:20:21,333
- Bulacan?
- Where in Bulacan, Jessica?

414
00:20:21,467 --> 00:20:23,933
<i> In Camalig... Gulod...</i>

415
00:20:24,067 --> 00:20:25,400
It has a brown gate.

416
00:20:25,533 --> 00:20:27,233
Hold on, hold on,
Slowly.

417
00:20:27,367 --> 00:20:28,300
I can't understand.

418
00:20:28,433 --> 00:20:31,833
You'll see Nita's store
before the house.

419
00:20:32,867 --> 00:20:34,867
- Nita's?
- Nita's?

420
00:20:36,433 --> 00:20:38,100
Uncle?

421
00:20:38,233 --> 00:20:39,133
Uncle?

422
00:20:39,267 --> 00:20:40,167
Jessica?

423
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:41,500
Hello?

424
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,033
She's gone.

425
00:20:43,167 --> 00:20:44,933
I'm sorry, the subscriber
cannot be reached.

426
00:20:46,167 --> 00:20:47,000
What happened, dear?

427
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:49,667
Did Abel get it?

428
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:52,600
Will he come here to pick us up?

429
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:57,300
I can't contact him, Dad.

430
00:20:57,433 --> 00:20:59,667
The line was cut.

431
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:02,967
But I'll try to call again, Dad.

432
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,000
Wait.

433
00:21:04,133 --> 00:21:07,033
Why don't you text him, dear?

434
00:21:07,167 --> 00:21:08,367
I'll try, Dad.

435
00:21:16,767 --> 00:21:17,833
Call her again.

436
00:21:17,967 --> 00:21:19,733
I'm sorry, the subscriber
cannot be reached.

437
00:21:19,867 --> 00:21:21,600
<i> - Please try again later.
-</i> She can't be reached anymore.

438
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:26,200
Gulod Street.

439
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:35,667
Dad.

440
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,300
It won't send.

441
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:43,633
Dad, it won't send.

442
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:45,000
Try it again.

443
00:21:46,267 --> 00:21:47,700
Try once more, Dear.

444
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:38,800
Jessica?

445
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:42,433
Dad.

446
00:22:45,033 --> 00:22:46,100
Jessica!

447
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:00,633
Jessica!

448
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:56,133
Manuel, I love you so much.

449
00:24:01,333 --> 00:24:02,967
I can't bear...

450
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:06,400
to lose you.

451
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:11,467
I'm sorry.

452
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:15,667
I'm sorry, but you getting back
together with Felma...

453
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:20,000
that will never happen.

454
00:24:23,167 --> 00:24:24,667
Manuel...

455
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:26,533
let's start over again.

456
00:24:27,567 --> 00:24:29,033
You...

457
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,267
me...

458
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:33,533
and Jessica.

459
00:24:33,667 --> 00:24:40,933
No one else.

460
00:24:41,067 --> 00:24:42,967
How long will you hurt
my daughter?

461
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:45,033
So that she'll learn her lesson
not to betray me.

462
00:24:45,167 --> 00:24:46,967
She's not betraying you, Hazel.

463
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:48,333
That's love!

464
00:24:48,467 --> 00:24:49,300
How about me, Manuel?

465
00:24:49,433 --> 00:24:50,567
When will you love me?

466
00:24:50,700 --> 00:24:52,200
I can't love you.

467
00:24:52,333 --> 00:24:54,367
Sis, what if she files a case?

468
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:57,367
That's better, we'll settle
everything in court.

469
00:24:57,500 --> 00:25:00,333
With just one testimony from
Manuel and Jessica,

470
00:25:00,467 --> 00:25:01,700
the case is over.

471
00:25:01,867 --> 00:25:03,300
Give me your passport
and your father's.

472
00:25:03,433 --> 00:25:05,933
I'll book our flight back
to Canada.

473
00:25:06,067 --> 00:25:08,367
They left the passports.

474
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:09,567
Manuel's...

475
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:11,533
Our passports aren't here.

476
00:25:12,933 --> 00:25:13,800
What?

477
00:25:13,933 --> 00:25:15,967
They're in Aunt Felma's house.
